page.t:
The Annihilator-class Star Dreadnaught is a 7.2 kilometer XXL capital ship manufactured by Kuat Drive Yards. Designed to provide capital ship supremacy to a fleet, it features unique axial ultra heavy dual turbolasers in addition to Dreadnaught standard-issue 720-teraton quad heavy turbolaser main batteries. For its size the Annihilator is very fast thanks to it's array of 33 engines, giving it the ability to hunt down all but the fastest capital ships.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Titan-class Star Destroyer is an XXL capital ship manufactured by Kuat Drive Yards, originally conceptualized as a merging of the Imperial and Allegiance classes onto a larger hull. The Titan is designed as an anti-capital battleship, and has minimal carrier capabilities. Its main axial batteries are 720-teraton Quad Heavy Turbolasers - most commonly seen on dreadnaughts, which are highly effective against other capital ships.

{1423090083,7}

{1423090083,2}

The Eclipse was the lead ship of the 17.5 kilometer Eclipse-class dreadnaught, the prototype of that class, and one of only two ships of the class to ever be built. Encased in a jet-black durasteel and quadranium alloyed hull, the immense ship was said to be the deadliest capital ship in the galaxy. By volume, the Eclipse was one of the largest warships ever built and the largest Star Destroyer ever, though in length it was somewhat shorter than the 19 kilometer Executor-class Star Dreadnaughts and Vengeance-class dreadnaughts.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Strident-class Star Defender is an XXL warship used by the New Republic Defense Fleet, produced by the Corellian Engineering Corporation.

{1423090083,5}

{1423090083,2}

The Procurator II-class Star Battlecruiser, was a 3.4 kilometer-long warship produced by Kuat Drive Yards in the final years before the Procurator-classes would be succeeded by the 4 kilometer-long Praetor-class Star Battlecruiser. The Procurator II-class featured refinements to armaments and hyperdrive systems made by KDY over the near 200 years that the Procurator-class was in production.

{1423090083,6}

{1423090083,2}

The Harrower II-class was a 2.3 kilometer-long Battlecruiser classed warship produced by Taerab Starship Manufacturing. The design was based on an early era model of the 800 meter-long Harrower class albeit upscaled for a much larger chassis.

{1423090083,9}

{1423090083,2}

The Mandator II-class Star Dreadnaught was a 8 kilometer-long XXL warship produced by Kuat Drive Yards that served in the centralized Republic Navy by 19 BBY. Having cut its ties to the Techno Union prior to the Clone Wars, Kuat Drive Yards began building starships for Republic use only. Among its new designs was the Mandator II-class, an upgrade of the prewar Mandator-class Star Dreadnaught, which had formed part of the Kuat sector's defenses in peace-time. These heavy vessels formed part of Supreme Chancellor Palpatine's newly centralized Republic Navy during the Clone Wars, along with KDY's other heavily armed, wedge-shaped warship designs.

This ship features a single L dock at the front of the ship that can hold one of the following ships: Arquitens Cruiser, Hammerhead Cruiser, Hardcell Frigate, Imperial Light Cruiser, Interceptor Frigate, Lancer Frigate, Nebulon B Frigate, Pelta II-class Frigate, Praetorian-class Frigate, Storm Commando Carrier, Teroch Cruiser, or Vigil Corvette.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Bellator-class Mark II receives a drastic increase in size, firepower, and shielding nearly allowing it to rival other dreadnaughts.
The Bellator-class is a warship produced by Kuat Drive Yards, which was in service to the Galactic Empire during its reign. The Bellator was a divergent design of the Mandator II-class Star Dreadnaught which KDY had previously produced for the Galactic Republic.

Compared to the Mandator II-class, the Bellator-class was built on an 800 meters shorter frame, was less armored and armed - but was much faster featuring a greatly improved hyperdrive and sublight speeds.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Lusankya, originally known as Executor II, was an Executor-class Star Dreadnaught built by Kuat Drive Yards, as the sister ship to the Executor, which was built at Fondor. As the ship had been surrendered to him, Wedge Antilles was the acting commander of the Lusankya and is now under the control of the New Republic.

As its primary purposed is planetary occupation, the Lusankya removes its long range turbolasers in order to allocate that power capacity towards expanded hangar capacity, increased point defence strength, and increased radar range.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Mandator III-class was based on the Mandator-class and Mandator II-class Star Dreadnaughts.

Unlike the Bellator-class dreadnaught, another Mandator successor design, the Mandator III-class dreadnaught was specifically designed to be a hulking weapons platform and was both longer and more heavily armed than its predecessors and its contemporary "cousin", featuring shields that rivaled that of the Executor-class. At 12,000 meters in length, it was essentially a scaled-up version of the Mandators.

This ship features custom L docks that can hold any of the following ships: Arquitens Cruiser, Hammerhead Cruiser, Hardcell Frigate, Imperial Light Cruiser, Interceptor Frigate, Lancer Frigate, Nebulon B Frigate, Pelta II-class Frigate, Praetorian-class Frigate, Storm Commando Carrier, Teroch Cruiser, or Vigil Corvette.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

Joking referred to by some as the Spicy Donut, the Gravatus-class is an aggressive modernization of the famous Lucrehulk class battleships from the Clone Wars.

Developed by Hoersch-Kessel Drive to counter the ever increasing numbers of Republic Star Dreadnaughts, the Gravatus-class sees a massive shift is design philosophy. removing all fighter facilities minus docks,reinforcing bulkheads and other critical areas, and the complete removal of all PD systems. All to allow room for a gargantuan arsenal of anti capital heavy proton torpedoes and weaponry.

{1423090083,6}

{1423090083,2}

The Mandator II-class Star Dreadnaught was a 8 kilometer-long XXL warship produced by Kuat Drive Yards that served in the centralized Republic Navy by 19 BBY. Having cut its ties to the Techno Union prior to the Clone Wars, Kuat Drive Yards began building starships for Republic use only. Among its new designs was the Mandator II-class, an upgrade of the prewar Mandator-class Star Dreadnaught, which had formed part of the Kuat sector's defenses in peace-time. These heavy vessels formed part of Supreme Chancellor Palpatine's newly centralized Republic Navy during the Clone Wars, along with KDY's other heavily armed, wedge-shaped warship designs.

This version has been overhauled by an Imperial Warlord in a traditional Imperial gray livery.

This ship features a single L dock at the front of the ship that can hold one of the following ships: Arquitens Cruiser, Hammerhead Cruiser, Hardcell Frigate, Imperial Light Cruiser, Interceptor Frigate, Lancer Frigate, Nebulon B Frigate, Pelta II-class Frigate, Praetorian-class Frigate, Storm Commando Carrier, Teroch Cruiser, or Vigil Corvette.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Mandator II-class Star Dreadnaught was a 8 kilometer-long XXL warship produced by Kuat Drive Yards that served in the centralized Republic Navy by 19 BBY. Having cut its ties to the Techno Union prior to the Clone Wars, Kuat Drive Yards began building starships for Republic use only. Among its new designs was the Mandator II-class, an upgrade of the prewar Mandator-class Star Dreadnaught, which had formed part of the Kuat sector's defenses in peace-time. These heavy vessels formed part of Supreme Chancellor Palpatine's newly centralized Republic Navy during the Clone Wars, along with KDY's other heavily armed, wedge-shaped warship designs.

This version has been captured by the Mandalorians, seeing its fore large dock removed in favor of two medium docks, and the Republic livery stripped, replaced with Mandalorian colors.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Mandator II-class Star Dreadnaught was a 8 kilometer-long XXL warship produced by Kuat Drive Yards that served in the centralized Republic Navy by 19 BBY. Having cut its ties to the Techno Union prior to the Clone Wars, Kuat Drive Yards began building starships for Republic use only. Among its new designs was the Mandator II-class, an upgrade of the prewar Mandator-class Star Dreadnaught, which had formed part of the Kuat sector's defenses in peace-time. These heavy vessels formed part of Supreme Chancellor Palpatine's newly centralized Republic Navy during the Clone Wars, along with KDY's other heavily armed, wedge-shaped warship designs.

This version was commissioned for the fabled 501st Legion, but never saw battle before the Clone Wars ended. It has remained in dry dock on Kamino since the end of the war.

This ship features a single L dock at the front of the ship that can hold one of the following ships: Arquitens Cruiser, Hammerhead Cruiser, Hardcell Frigate, Imperial Light Cruiser, Interceptor Frigate, Lancer Frigate, Nebulon B Frigate, Pelta II-class Frigate, Praetorian-class Frigate, Storm Commando Carrier, Teroch Cruiser, or Vigil Corvette.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Bellator-class Mark IIA receives a drastic increase in size, firepower, and shielding nearly allowing it to rival other dreadnaughts. Compared to the Mark II, the Mark IIA was designed for a warlord who desired an ancient Imperial gray aesthetic.

The Bellator-class Star Dreadnaught was a 7.2 kilometer-long XXL warship produced by Kuat Drive Yards, which was in service to the Galactic Empire during its reign. The Bellator was a divergent design of the Mandator II-class Star Dreadnaught which KDY had previously produced for the Galactic Republic. Compared to the Mandator II-class, the Bellator-class was built on an 800 meters shorter frame, was less armored and armed - but was much faster featuring a greatly improved hyperdrive and sublight speeds.

This version is has seen use by the Imperial Intelligence Agency, seeing the stark white hull and turrets replaced with a dark grey color.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Compellor-class battlecruiser is an XXL warship produced by Kuat Drive Yards. Developed as part of the Pellor Project, the Compellor-class was designed as successor to the successful Titan-class Star Destroyer.

The Compellor-class sacrifices many of its hangar bays compared to its sister ship, the Impellor-class, in order to focus on raw firepower.

{1423090083,5}

{1423090083,2}

The Impellor-class battlecruiser is an XXL carrier produced by Kuat Drive Yards. Developed as part of the Pellor Project, the Impellor-class was designed to combine firepower of two ISD II with the fighter complement of two ISD I in just one ship.

{1423090083,5}

{1423090083,2}

The Praetor Mark II-class Battlecruiser is a 4.8 kilometer-long XXL warship produced by Kuat Drive Yards produced for the Imperial Navy in 19 BBY. The Praetor Mark II was designed as a follow-up to the smaller Republic-era Praetor-class Star Battlecruiser.

Only a few ships of this class were built, as Imperial doctrine favored both the larger dreadnaught classed designs and smaller Imperial Star Destroyers. In the end most of the Praetor Mark II-class ships produced would go on to spend their service life in drydock assigned to guarding Imperial Core Worlds.

{1423090083,6}

{1423090083,2}

The Veragitor-class Battlecruiser, also known as a Republic Battlecruiser, is a Clone Wars era re-imagining of the ancient Sundari-class Dreadnaught. When pressed for an answer to larger Separatist dreadnaughts' success against their Venator-class Star Destroyers, Grand Army of the Republic designers looked back through history and found records detailing the Sundari-class of the Mandalorian Wars.

The Veragitor-class did not manage to enter production until 20 BBY and only saw minimal combat in the year before the Clone Wars ended. Many examples have spent their entire life cycle in orbital mothball.

Worried by signs of aggression from the Independent Commerce Guild, Kaminoan planetary defense forces looked to their vast boneyard; the Veragitor-class was once more found to be the answer to the Venator-class's shortcomings.

{1423090083,5}

{1423090083,2}

The Annihilator-class Inquisitor Dreadnaught is a 7.2 kilometer XXL capital ship manufactured by Kuat Drive Yards. Designed to provide capital ship supremacy to a fleet, it features unique axial ultra heavy dual turbolasers in addition to Dreadnaught standard-issue 720-teraton quad heavy turbolaser main batteries. For its size the Annihilator is very fast thanks to it's array of 33 engines, giving it the ability to hunt down all but the fastest capital ships.

This variant has been refitted by Sith Inquisitorial Command and features improved armor plating and enhanced engine performance.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Harrower II-class Inquisitor was a 2.3 kilometer-long Battlecruiser classed warship produced by Taerab Starship Manufacturing. The design was based on an early era model of the 800 meter-long Harrower class albeit upscaled for a much larger chassis.

This variant has been refitted by Sith Inquisitorial Command and features improved armor plating and enhanced engine performance.

{1423090083,7}

{1423090083,2}

The MoH-96 is a 720-teraton spherical quad-barreled heavy turbolaser turret designed by a long forgotten Mandalorian shipwright and modernized by MandalMotors.

Designed for installation on Sundari-class Dreadnaughts.

{1423090083,2}

The SX-4-96 is a 720-teraton spherical quad-barreled heavy turbolaser turret designed by a long forgotten Mandalorian shipwright and modernized by Grand Army of the Republic engineers.

Designed for installation on Veragitor-class Battlecruiser.

{1423090083,2}

The Golan IV-class Battle Station is an anti-dreadnaught defence platform manufactured by Golan Arms with hangar space for 32 Small and 8 Medium craft.

Built as a more powerful successor to the Golan III, the Golan IV was larger and better armed; nearly that double a Golan III in every metric.

A Golan IV with all of its modules can act as every kind of Equipment Dock as well as and an Admin module for the purposes of the Maintenance system.

{1423090083,1}
{1423090083,2}

The Executor-class Star Dreadnaught, colloquially known as the Executor-class Super Star Destroyer, Executor-class Star Destroyer or simply Super Star Destroyer, is a heavy warship class in the Star Dreadnaught league, often used as command ships and flagships in the Imperial Navy. At their prime, they were among the largest vessels in the galaxy, and were almost invincible in combat, although they were costly to operate.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Bellator-class Dreadnaught is a divergent design in the Mandator-series of Star Dreadnaught that served as a warship in the Imperial Navy. It is a class of large-scale dreadnaught that was manufactured by Kuat Drive Yards and served as a flagship in numerous Imperial fleets across the galaxy during the reign of Emperor Palpatine. Thanks to recent conflicts, a shortage of materials and manpower, and the destruction or capture of key shipyards, few Bellators remain in service.

{1423090083,5}

{1423090083,2}

The prototype of the class of Super Star Destroyer that eventually became the Executor-class Star Dreadnaught. This schematic was acquired by criminal lords after fall of the Empire and sold to interested parties. While it lacks many of the improvements implemented in the final version of the Executor, it is still a formidible warship.

{1423090083,4}

{1423090083,2}

The Praetor-class Battlecruiser is an XXL warship that was produced by Kuat Drive Yards in the final years of the Galactic Republic. Examples of the class seen today have been refurbished to serve in wealthy militias and corporate security forces.

{1423090083,6}

{1423090083,2}

In the early months of the Clone Wars, the Republic Navy was plagued by a new and terrifying threat: a Subjugator-class Battlecruiser, the Malevolence. Initially the Republic had difficulty in tracking the Malevolence as its advanced axial Ion Cannons were capable of projecting a massive blast which disabled any vessel caught in its wake, and even entire fleets of Republic Star Destroyers fell to the following barrage of missiles and laser fire. The Republic's first several encounters with the Malevolence resulted in a complete loss of Republic assets, and only a handful of survivors.

However, with the intelligence acquired by those survivors, Republic forces under General Anakin Skywalker were able to disable the Malevolence with a large-scale bomber strike, and on-board sabotage forced the ship to crash into the Dead Moon of Antar, finally destroying it.

Despite being wildly successful in its first engagements, the Separatists kept their remaining Subjugators away from the frontlines except as a last result, fearing additional losses of these resource-intensive ships; those remaining Subjugators disappeared entirely after the Clone Wars.

Following the end of the Galactic Civil War, and the growing hostilities between the Corporate Sector Authority and Independent Commerce Guild, it has been rumored that these massive ships have once again been seen in supermassive shipyards.

{1423090083,5}

{1423090083,2}
